text: It's genuinely insane how literally every single change Elon Musk has done to this website has made it actively worse in some way, no matter how minor, it's almost impressive. I think it is somewhat comparable to twitter's Khrushchev era. The Indian guy before him was Malenkov.

Jack era was shitlib Stalinism. You say the n-word, your account disappears. Call someone the r-word, banned. You knew you had to keep silent and allude w/o spelling. Now it seems you can misgender people unpunished, use the f-word, but some people still get randomly suspended.

A sort of vague anxiety at testing the limits of free speech, being unsure if what you say can actually get your account taken down or not. If my model is right, I predict after Musk there will be a Brezhnev era of increased but more opaque censorship and a "pleasant" stagnation.
